  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Mental Health: Integrated Innovations to Improve Treatments and Expand Access to Care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heartland Alliance Colombia (HAC) and the Institute for Peace Promotion and Injury/Violence Prevention (CISALVA)  will conduct initial research into indigenous conceptions of distress, to identify areas of overlap with western conceptions of depression and PTSD, and to develop assessment measures based on community conceptions of well-being. Additionally, HAC and CISALVA will research suicide patterns, practices and precipitating factors to develop a prevention strategy consistent with best practices for reducing suicide contagion.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will develop a time-limited cognitive-behavioral intervention for depression and Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD), combined with culturally-appropriate suicide education and prevention for indigenous communities in the Choco region of Colombia that are affected by paramilitary violence related to resource extraction.</narrative>
  </description>
